// Scarlet Goldfinch / ClickFix Paste-and-Run Process Chain
//
// EQL sequence catching the behavioral process lineage created by paste-and-run
// delivery mechanisms. Targets the structural invariant that survives across
// 7+ documented Scarlet Goldfinch epochs of command-line obfuscation evolution.
//
// Detection design rationale: investigation.md
// Lab testing and adjustments: validation.md
//
// Target platform: Elastic Security
// Telemetry source: Elastic Defend (endpoint.events.process)
// Rule type: Event Correlation (EQL)
//
// Required ECS fields:
//   process.parent.name
//   process.name
//   process.entity_id
//   process.parent.entity_id
//   process.pe.original_file_name (fallback for renamed binaries)
//
// MITRE ATT&CK:
//   T1204.004  User Execution: Malicious Copy and Paste (primary)
//   T1059.001  Command and Scripting Interpreter: PowerShell
//   T1059.003  Command and Scripting Interpreter: Windows Command Shell
//   T1218.005  System Binary Proxy Execution: Mshta
//   T1105      Ingress Tool Transfer
//   T1027      Obfuscated Files or Information
//
// Known limitations (see investigation.md and validation.md):
//   - Intermediate parent processes (e.g., forfiles between explorer and cmd) break stage 1
//   - Invoke-CimMethod / WMI reparenting bypasses the explorer.exe parent match
//   - FileFix variants produce different lineage
//   - Administrator Run-dialog workflows produce known false positives
//
// Triage: pair with companion KQL rule (detection-lolbin.kql) for LOLBin egress.
// Co-occurrence on same host within 2 minutes = high confidence indicator.

sequence with maxspan=2m
  [process where
      process.parent.name == "explorer.exe"
      and process.name in (
          "cmd.exe",
          "powershell.exe",
          "pwsh.exe",
          "wscript.exe",
          "cscript.exe"
      )] by process.entity_id

  [process where
      process.parent.name in (
          "cmd.exe",
          "powershell.exe",
          "pwsh.exe",
          "wscript.exe",
          "cscript.exe"
      )
      and (
          process.name in (
              "mshta.exe",
              "curl.exe",
              "certutil.exe",
              "bitsadmin.exe",
              "forfiles.exe",
              "hh.exe",
              "regsvr32.exe",
              "finger.exe"
          )
          or process.pe.original_file_name in (
              "mshta.exe",
              "curl.exe",
              "CertUtil.exe",
              "bitsadmin.exe",
              "forfiles.exe",
              "finger.exe"
          )
      )] by process.parent.entity_id
